  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KVStreamlet<K,V>, Streamlet<KeyValue<K,V>>

    public class KVFlatMapStreamlet<R,K,V>
extends BaseKVStreamlet<K,V>
    KVFlatMapStreamlet represents a KVStreamlet that is made up of applying the user supplied flatMap function to each element of the parent streamlet and flattening out the result. The only difference between this and FlatMapStreamlet is that KVFlatMapStreamlet ensures that resulting elements are of type KeyValue.
